Data cleaning is the process of finding and correcting incomplete, inconsistent, duplicated, invalid, or incorrectly formatted data before analysis or model training.

A machine-learning model trained on poor-quality data will usually produce poor-quality results.

```text
Poor data → Poor patterns → Poor predictions
```

