## 3. Why Data Cleaning Matters

Machine-learning algorithms do not automatically understand whether data is sensible.

A model may accept:

```text
Age = -5
Age = 250
Salary = "unknown"
City = "dubai"
City = "Dubai "
```

Even though these values are inconsistent or invalid.

Data cleaning improves:

* Accuracy
* Reliability
* Reproducibility
* Model stability
* Feature quality
* Reporting quality
* Debugging

A common machine-learning workflow is:

```text
Raw data
   |
   v
Inspection
   |
   v
Cleaning
   |
   v
Validation
   |
   v
Exploratory analysis
   |
   v
Feature engineering
   |
   v
Model training
```

