## 7. Missing Values

Pandas usually represents missing numerical data as:

```text
NaN
```

Check missing values:

```python
customers.isna()
```

Count missing values per column:

```python
missing_counts = customers.isna().sum()
```

Calculate missing percentages:

```python
missing_percentage = (
    customers.isna().mean() * 100
)
```

Why this works:

```text
True  → 1
False → 0
```

The mean of Boolean values gives the missing fraction.

