### Duplicate Entities

Two rows may represent the same customer even when they are not identical.

Example:

| Customer ID | Name | Spending |
| ----------: | ---- | -------: |
|         102 | Sara |     3200 |
|         102 | Sara |     3500 |

These are not exact duplicate rows, but the repeated customer ID may violate the dataset’s rules.

Check duplicate IDs:

```python
customers[
    customers["customer_id"].duplicated(
        keep=False
    )
]
```

Remove duplicate IDs:

```python
customers = customers.drop_duplicates(
    subset=["customer_id"],
    keep="last",
)
```

Choosing `first` or `last` must be based on business meaning.

