## 18. Validating Numerical Ranges

A valid customer age might be:

[
0 \leq \text{age} \leq 120
]

Create an invalid-age mask:

```python
invalid_age_mask = (
    (customers["age"] < 0)
    | (customers["age"] > 120)
)
```

View invalid rows:

```python
invalid_ages = customers[
    invalid_age_mask
]
```

Replace invalid ages with missing values:

```python
customers.loc[
    invalid_age_mask,
    "age",
] = pd.NA
```

Then fill using the median:

```python
customers["age"] = customers["age"].fillna(
    customers["age"].median()
)
```

